Package: calamineR
Title: Fast Excel File Reader Using Rust
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maximilian", "Manek", email = "maximilian.manek@hotmail.de",
                  role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Juan Antonio Monroy Kuhn", email = "amonroykuhn@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Johann Tuffe", role = "aut", comment = "calamine Rust library"),
    person("Authors of the dependent Rust crates", role = "aut", comment = "see inst/AUTHORS file")
    )
Description: High-performance Excel file reader supporting xlsx, xlsm, xlsb,
    xls, and ods formats. Built on the Rust 'calamine' library, providing
    significantly faster read times compared to pure R implementations.
    Supports reading sheet names, dimensions, and data as data frames.
    Can optionally fill merged cells with the top-left cell value.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/MaxManek1110/calamineR
